 impersonate the user to the real service as well (thus being a proper MITM).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There exist a number of one-message webauth authentication mechanisms that
 are widely deployed; we cannot forbid their use, we can only document their
 security considerations, namely: that they depend entirely on the TLS server
 PKI for their security.
